name: DIAMOND
reference: Birch 1966 and Fujihisa (from Fried & Howard 2000) V(P), Skinner 1966 V(T), Victor 1962 Cp

name: GLAUCOPHANE
reference: from Evans (1990, Lithos) update to Cp coefficients by Fang Huang, 2018

name: KFELDSPAR
reference: Consistent with Sverjensky et al. (1991) June 24, 2020

name: ALBITE
reference: Consistent with Sverjensky et al. (1991) June 24, 2020, Above D1 line needed to compute stable ordering relative to high albite, using Landau-type function of Salje et al. (1985) in external ALBITE routine

name: ANTIGORITE
reference: Revised volume coefficients consistent with Hilairet et al. (2006) and Yang et al. (2014); half of the Berman formula, as used in DATA0

name: PHLOGOPITE
reference: Consistent with Sverjensky et al. (1991) June 24, 2020

name: PARAGONITE
reference: Consistent with Sverjensky et al. (1991) June 24, 2020

name: GRAPHITE
reference: Entropy increased by .7 J/mole/K, Hanfland et al 1989 V(P),  Skinner 1966 V(T) Robie Cp

name: BARITE
reference: G, H, S, Cp, V from Helgeson et al. (1978); volume coefficients from Merry (pers. comm.), fit to data from Sawada & Takeuchi (1990) & Crichton et al. (2011); consistent with Santamaria-Perez et al. (2011) to 25 GPa and 1,000 C.
